HEADWORD: Strewing
<hw>Strew"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of scattering or spreading.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything that is, or may be, strewed; -- used
chiefly in the plural.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strewment</ent>⟦br⟧
